<p><font face="Arial" size="5"><b>IntraWeb 6 presents.....</b></font></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p align="center"><b><font face="Arial" size="7">I</font><font face="Arial" size="4">ntra</font><font face="Arial" size="7">W</font><font face="Arial" size="4">eb</font><font face="Arial" size="7">P</font><font face="Arial" size="4">ages</font></b></p>
<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font face="Arial">IntraWeb 6 expands it's PageMode
functionality to bring you IWP's (IntraWeb Pages) which allow you to design
webpages with your favorite web designer application and let IW add the dynamic
content to it.</font></p>
<p align="left"><font face="Arial">The difference between this new feature and
what existed in previous versions is that you now trigger the functionality from
the static pages. That is, you design the pages and then IntraWeb processes them
inserting the controls and implementing the server-side actions. If you are
familiar with PageMode applications and TemplateProcessors, you know that you
design the form and associate a template file with it. The form then replaces
the tags in the template (the form requests the template in some way). You can
think of IWP's as the reverse, i.e., the template requests the form in your
project.&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="left"><FONT FACE="Arial">Two key differences are that:</FONT></p>
<p align="left"><FONT FACE="Arial">1. You do not need to produce dynamic content
or associate a form with each template (IWP) file. For example this file does
not have a corresponding form in the IWPDemo project.</FONT></p>
<p align="left"><FONT FACE="Arial">2. You do not need to place ANY code in your
ISAPI or DSO WebBroker application to return contents. Just drop two components
on the WebModule.</FONT></p>
<p align="left"><FONT FACE="Arial">Note: Although in this example filenames with
the .iwp extension are used, you can use any type of extension, just as long as
you associate it with the correct application (see the manual for more
information).</FONT></p>
<p align="left"><font face="Arial">To see how all this works, <a href="step1.iwp"> click here</a></font></p>
